.TH "WISWA" "1" "Apr 18, 2026" "0.2.1" "wiswa"
.SH NAME
wiswa \- wiswa v0.2.1
.SH INSTALLATION
.sp
We recommend a \fBglobal\fP install so \fBwiswa\fP and \fBwiswa\-mcp\fP are on your
\fBPATH\fP from any working directory:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
uv tool install wiswa
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Or with pipx:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
pipx install wiswa
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
If you prefer not to install globally, add Wiswa as a \fBdevelopment
dependency\fP of your project—for example \fBuv add \-\-group dev wiswa\fP, or list
\fBwiswa\fP under \fBdependency\-groups.dev\fP in \fBpyproject.toml\fP and install
inside the project virtual environment with your usual workflow.
.SS wiswa
.sp
Generate and maintain projects with Jsonnet.
.sp
Usage
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
wiswa [OPTIONS] [FILE]
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Options
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-cache\-time <cache_time>
Cache expiration time in seconds.
.INDENT 7.0
.TP
.B Default
\fB600\fP
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
